would mean something starting

00:12:18.710 --> 00:12:21.120
around the 1820s, whatever.

00:12:21.120 --> 00:12:24.260
People describe Schubert a
little bit as the first romantic.

00:12:24.260 --> 00:12:28.670 position:56%
Quite frankly I think these labels
are really poisonous, because to me,

00:12:28.670 --> 00:12:35.980
Monteverdi, and Bach, and Handel,
and Castello are just as romantic

00:12:35.980 --> 00:12:38.360
as Rachmaninoff and Tchaikovsky.

00:12:38.360 --> 00:12:40.880
And in fact, it's more direct.

00:12:40.880 --> 00:12:42.600
The earlier the music, certainly

00:12:42.600 --> 00:12:48.020
in 1790s actually is a more
direct correlation to how we,

00:12:48.020 --> 00:12:52.060
as human beings, express
ourselves with our emotions.

00:12:52.060 --> 00:12:54.890
I mean, the thing about
Rachmaninoff and Tchaikovsky,

00:12:54.890 --> 00:12:59.160
you'll have a slow movement
which lasts for 15 or 20 minutes,

00:12:59.160 --> 00:13:02.210
and that's really all it
does for 15 or 20 minutes.

